ign=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=qhue>Qhue</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bitter Enchanter. Please don't feed the troll.</span><br>  Posts: 43<br> <font color=#330000>(6/10/04 10:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19472.topic&index=122>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/psifi_98/qhuetalk.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: pulling...</span><hr size=1> First of all I was NOT the origin of the % mana thing.  That was posted on another summary of the event post.  Its a stupid concept because then the bard with the LOWEST manapool could fade more often and bards would be forever dueling enchanters to get &quot;curse of the simple mind&quot; cast on them and wearing kobold jester hats.   As an enchanter in my guild last night remarked:<br>
<br>
Enchanter: &quot;I'm bugged! I'm at 60% mana but I cant cast spells, it says I'm OOM!&quot;<br>
<br>
Guild : &quot;Dumbass yer naked, put some clothes on&quot;<br>
<br>
Secondly I only referred to Fading Memories and it being looked at for problems designing content.  As in NEW content where designers would really like to include such-and-such as part of a static encounter but couldn't because they knew it would be trivial for a bard monk combo to split it all away.  Txevu already has to have complex triggered scripts to allow for any multiple mob encounter where the mobs are pre-targetable due to FM.  Simply having FM not work in a few instances would keep things more creative and also keep Bards a bit more excited.    <br>
<br>
Talk to the rogues who now, for the first time in ages, have to WORRY about being seen and how much more exciting it makes it to sneak around with that possibility out there.  Is it so bad that bards have to be careful about their aggro too in a few potential cases?  I'd think having a 100% no fail security blanket around all the time would make things just a bit dull.<br>
<br>
Finally we enchanters do have a message board, but do you really expect that the master's of illusion would keep our secrets somwhere that a bunch of wannabe illusionist chord-pluckers could find?!?    In all seriousness the enchanter boards at www.therunes.net are probably the most common talking point these days.  The original Enchanter board became Castersrealm and stopped being even remotely useful for enchanters about 3+ years ago.  Its taken awhile for a suitable replacement to come forward. <p>Qhue Oculorum, Master Scholar and High Enchanter of Tunare</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=qhue>Qhue</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0> at: 6/10/04 10:37 am<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#330000>- </font><a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall>The Concert Hall - Message Boards</a><font color=#330000> - </font><a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage>Backstage</a><font color=#330000> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 7.31p<br>Copyright ©1999-2003 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  